Infrastructure Development Said to Hire Banks for Dollar Loan

-- B y   E m i   U r a b e   a n d   Y u s u k e   M i y a z a w a
-- 
2011-04-15T00:26:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/infrastructure-development-said-to-hire-banks-for-dollar-loan.html
Infrastructure Development Finance
Co., an Indian lender to power and road projects, hired three
banks to help it borrow $200 million in a five-year  term loan ,
according to a person with direct knowledge of the transaction.  Bank of Nova Scotia, Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ Ltd. and
Goldman Sachs Group Inc. are arranging the facility, which may
pay interest of 1.75 percentage points more than London
interbank offered rate, said the person, who asked not to be
identified as the information is private.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Emi Urabe in  Tokyo  at 
 eurabe@bloomberg.net 
Yusuke Miyazawa in Tokyo at 
 ymiyazawa3@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will McSheehy at 
 wmcsheehy@bloomberg.net . 